title: Haiti Gang Shoots at Protesters, Killing Several in Port-au-Prince
description: The shooting reflects escalating tensions as vigilante groups push back against gangs in areas around Port-au-Prince.

title: Hailstorm in Germany Rips Through a Town, Damaging Buildings and Cars
description: An estimated 80 percent of buildings were damaged during a hailstorm in Bad Bayersoien, Germany.

title: With Prigozhin Dead, Russia’s Wagner Faces an Uncertain Future
description: It could be hard for the Kremlin to find a way to neutralize the mercenary group after Yevgeny Prigozhin’s death while retaining its fighting power and geopolitical links.

title: Zimbabwe’s Neighbors Cast Doubt on Elections That Gave Mnangagwa the Win
description: The main regional bloc in southern Africa and the African Union declined to rubber stamp the elections and cast doubt on a vote that led to President Emmerson Mnangagwa’s re-election.

title: After Prigozhin’s Death, Mourners Gather at Wagner Memorial in Moscow
description: Hundreds of people have placed flowers and other tributes on a sidewalk near Red Square in Moscow.

title: U.S. Commerce Secretary Faces a Wide Range of Issues in China
description: The secretary said she planned to discuss U.S. technology controls, commercial disputes and opportunities for doing more business in her visits to Beijing and Shanghai this week.

title: Spanish Soccer Chief Finds His Defenders Backing Away
description: Luis Rubiales was widely condemned for kissing a player after the Spanish women’s team won the World Cup, but retained a few public supporters. Many now appear to be reconsidering.

title: Months After Earthquake, Syrians Feel Forgotten
description: In northwestern Syria, a devastating quake six months ago compounded the damage of years of civil war. U.S. lawmakers just visited for the first time in a decade.

title: Jacksonville Dollar General Shooting: What We Know
description: Three people, all Black, were fatally shot in a dollar store before the gunman, a white man, killed himself. Investigators are treating the killing as a hate crime.

title: Canada Revisits Ancient Prevention Tactics to Battle Wildfires
description: A movement to fight wildfires by making forests more resilient and, in some cases, deliberately setting blazes is gaining ground in Canada.

title: Russia Officially Confirms Prigozhin’s Death
description: Russian investigators said genetic tests showed that the Wagner chief, Yevgeny V. Prigozhin, who led a brief mutiny against Moscow’s military leadership, was among the victims of a plane crash last week.

title: Russia Says Ukraine Fired Drones at Three Regions
description: The frequency of drone attacks inside Russia has increased in recent weeks, bringing the war to areas deep inside Russian territory.

title: Western Banks Help Fund Blacklisted Oligarch’s Charity
description: Konstantin Malofeyev’s foundation funds orphanages in occupied Ukraine. He denies that a child-removal program there is a war crime: “All of this is fake.”

title: A Former French President Gives a Voice to Obstinate Russian Sympathies
description: Remarks by Nicolas Sarkozy have raised fears that Europe’s pro-Putin chorus may grow louder as Ukraine’s plodding counteroffensive puts pressure on Western resolve.

title: The Joys of Sketching Birds
description: Times readers were invited to share their drawings of the avian life around them. Here are more of our favorites.

title: U.S. Marines Killed in Air Crash in Australia
description: The Osprey aircraft, with 23 people on board, crashed during a joint training exercise near Darwin, in the north of Australia. Several others were seriously injured.

title: Thailand’s Marijuana Business Is Growing Despite Regulatory Risks
description: The country’s legal marijuana business — a rarity in Asia — is struggling with oversupply, illegal imports and regulatory ambiguity. Investors are piling in anyway.
